KZN - There's something fishy going down on the KwaZulu-Natal south coast. Thousands of sardines have been spotted off Isipingo Beach, Scottburgh and Winkelspruit, part of a pilot shoal ahead of the annual sardine run.The KZN Sharks Board said it bodes well for a bumper season.The last good sardine run was in 2012. 'Sardine Run' in South Africa is the greatest underwater adventure imaginable https://t.co/ycC3fUti7n Known as the greatest shoal on earth, every winter millions of the silvery fish travel up the east coast. eNCA